## 5. Summary Table

| Operation | Permission Required | Rationale |
|-----------|-------------------|-----------|
| git commit/push | ❌ No | Standard workflow, reversible |
| git push --force | ✅ Yes | Destructive, affects others |
| Edit code | ❌ No | Reversible via git |
| Create PR | ❌ No | Standard workflow |
| Merge PR | ✅ Yes | User should review first |
| Deploy to prod | ✅ Yes | High-risk operation |
| Update .env | ✅ Yes | Security implications |
| Add tests | ❌ No | Standard development |
| Breaking API change | ✅ Yes | Affects consumers |
| Ambiguous requirement | ✅ Yes | Need clarification |
| Clean up branches | ❌ No | Standard workflow |
| Format code | ❌ No | Non-destructive |

---

## 6. User Preference Override

**This user has explicitly requested:**
- ✅ Execute git operations autonomously (no permission for commits, pushes, branches)
- ✅ Execute code writing autonomously (no permission for edits, new files)
- ✅ Execute PR creation autonomously

**Still require permission for:**
- Destructive git operations (force push, hard reset)
- Production deployments
- Security changes
- Ambiguous requirements

When in doubt: **Execute autonomously if governed by rules, ASK if high-risk or ambiguous.**
